[File:Lin Biao2.jpg|130px]] || \u6797\u5f6a || [[Lin Biao]]\n|-\n| 341 || [[File:Lu Jingru.jpg|130px]] || \u76e7\u93e1\u5982 || [[Lu Jingru]]\n|-\n| 342 || [[File:Lu Yongchuan.jpg|130px]] || \u76e7\u7528\u5ddd || [[Lu Yongchuan]]\n|-\n| 343 || [[File:Lu Zhonglin.jpg|130px]] || \u9e7f\u937e\u9e9f || [[Lu Zhonglin]]\n|}\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Japanese-language books]]\n[[Category:Republic of China (1912\u20131949)]]\n[[Category:1941 non-fiction books]]\n[[Category:Biographical dictionaries]]\n[[Category:China\u2013Japan relations]]\n[[Category:Reorganized National Government of China]]\n[[Category:Mengjiang]]\n[[Category:Asahi Shimbun Company]]\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\n{{Chinese|t=\u6700\u65b0\u652f\u90a3\u8981\u4eba\u50b3|s=\u6700\u65b0\u652f\u90a3\u8981\u4eba\u4f20|p=Zu\u00ecx\u012bn Zh\u012b\u200bn\u00e0 Y\u00e0or\u00e9n Zhu\u00e0n|w=Tsui-hsin Chih-na Yao-jen Chuan|kanji=\u6700\u65b0\u652f\u90a3\u8981\u4eba\u4f1d|romaji=Saishin Shina Y\u014djin Den}}\n'''''The Most Recent Biographies of Important Chinese People''''' ({{zh|t=\u6700\u65b0\u652f\u90a3\u8981\u4eba\u50b3}}, {{lang-ja|\u6700\u65b0\u652f\u90a3\u8981\u4eba\u4f1d}}) is a \"[[Who's Who]]\" on prominent individuals in the [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]], compiled in [[Empire of Japan|Japan]] by ''[[Asahi Shimbun]]''<ref>{{cite book|author = T\u014da Mondai Ch\u014dsakai|title=Saishin Shina y\u014djinden (The Most Recent Biographies of Important Chinese People)|location=Tokyo|publisher={{w|Asahi Shimbun}}|year=1941|oclc=23310651}}</ref> during the [[Second Sino-Japanese War]]. Published on 2 February 1941, the work references 343 contemporary notables in the [[Kuomintang]] and the [[Nationalist government]], the [[Communist Party of China|Chinese Communist Party]], the pro-Japanese [[Wang Jingwei regime]] and [[Mengjiang]], and independent politicians and celebrities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://catalog.digitalarchives.tw/item/00/10/74/d4.html|title=The Most Recent Biographies of Important Chinese People|language=zh|website=Taiwan e-Learning & Digital Archives Program|access-date=26 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nA digitization of the reference work can be found on the website of the [[National Diet Library]] of Japan,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dl.ndl.go.jp/info:ndljp/pid/1123795|title=The Most Recent Biographies of Important Chinese People|language=ja|website=National Diet Library Digital Collection|access-date=26 March 2019}}</ref> the full list of biographies follows.\n\n== Biographies ==\n{| style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n|  style=\"text-align:left; width:50%; vertical-align:top;\"|\n\n=== 1 to 25 ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! \u2116 !! Photo !! Name<br/>([[Chinese characters|Chinese]]) !! Name<br/>([[Pinyin|romanization]])\n|-\n| 1 || [[File:Alataneqier.jpg|130px]] || \u963f\u52d2\u5766\u9102\u9f4a\u723e || [[Alataneqier]]\n|-\n| 2 || [[File:Yin Rugeng3.jpg|130px]] || \u6bb7\u6c5d\u8015 || [[Yin Rugeng]]\n|-\n| 3 || [[File:Yin Tong.jpg|130px]] || \u6bb7\u540c || [[Yin Tong]]\n|-\n| 4 || [[File:Yu Xuezhong.jpg|130px]] || \u4e8e\u5b78\u5fe0 || [[Yu Xuezhong]]\n|-\n| 5 || [[File:Yu Pinqing.jpg|130px]] || \u4e8e\u54c1\u537f || [[Yu Pinqing]]\n|-\n| 6 || [[File:Yu Youren.jpg|130px]] || \u4e8e\u53f3\u4efb || [[Yu Youren]]\n|-\n| 7 || [[File:Wu Guting.jpg|130px]] || \u70cf\u53e4\u5ef7 || [[Wu Guting]]\n|-\n| 8 || [[File:Wei Lihuang.jpg|130px]] || \u885b\u7acb\u714c || [[Wei Lihuang]]\n|-\n| 9 || [[File:Yuan Lvdeng.jpg|130px]] || \u8881\u79ae\u6566|| [[Yuan Ludeng]]\n|-\n| 10 || [[File:Yan Xishan4.jpg|130px]] || \u95bb\u932b\u5c71 || [[Yan Xishan]]\n|-\n| 11 || [[File:Wang Yitang3.jpg|130px]] || \u738b\u63d6\u5510 || [[Wang Yitang]]\n|-\n| 12 || [[File:Wang Yintai.jpg|130px]] || \u738b\u852d\u6cf0 || [[Wang Yintai]]\n|-\n| 13 || [[File:Wang Yongquan.jpg|130px]] || \u738b\u6c38\u6cc9 || [[Wang Yongquan]]\n|-\n| 14 || [[File:Wang Jiazhen.jpg|130px]] || \u738b\u5bb6\u6968 || [[Wang Jiazhen]]\n|-\n| 15 || [[File:Wang Jingqi.j